Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta. Halve,
peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides
of the length of the courgette. Stop when you get to the spongy centre. Finely chop
the @chives{1}(finely chopped with scissors if easier). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the @reserved pasta water{100%ml} for the sauce, then
drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the #pan{}, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it
sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot,
add the courgette ribbons and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until softened,
~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}. Pop the cooked greens into a large #bowl{} and cover with #foil{} to
keep warm.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and reserved pasta water, then simmer until
reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}. Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and heat through
until piping hot, then season with @pepper{}.

Stir through the chives and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Add the cooked pasta to your sauce along with half the greens and stir together. Add a
splash of @water{} to loosen if needed.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice,
salt and pepper if needed.

Serve the creamy pasta in #bowls{} with the remaining greens on top. Finish with a
sprinkle of the remaining hard Italian style cheese. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to add bacon lardons to your meal, before you add the
> shallot to the pan, add the @?British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until
> golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the shallot to the bacon continue with the rest of the
> recipe as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw
> meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.